00:54:47.870 --> 00:54:49.170
&gt;&gt; Did you have a question, sir?

00:54:49.170 --> 00:54:54.090 position:56%
&gt;&gt; If I may follow up on that
point, Primo Levi is a hero of mine,

00:54:54.090 --> 00:54:58.820
kind of personal professional
mentor in this fashion.

00:54:58.820 --> 00:55:03.710 position:56%
He seems to be one of the few people
who have taken on, as you said,

00:55:03.710 --> 00:55:09.610
that existential issue of
Europe ended at Auschwitz.

00:55:09.610 --> 00:55:12.120 position:56%
The civilization ended at Auschwitz,

00:55:12.120 --> 00:55:14.530
that one full statement
you made earlier.

00:55:14.530 --> 00:55:18.790
Given the Nazis' belief
that the Jews

00:55:18.790 --> 00:55:24.170
and Judaism undermine the
natural race, conflict

00:55:24.170 --> 00:55:27.480
and racial progression
that they believed in,

00:55:27.480 --> 00:55:32.600
Primo Levi to me seems-- as a
person who really speaks to that

00:55:32.600 --> 00:55:34.760
and challenges that in a deep way.

00:55:34.760 --> 00:55:38.030
However, I'm not adequate to
really understand how he does

00:55:38.030 --> 00:55:40.820
that effectively, he
does that for me.

00:55:40.820 --> 00:55:45.600
Could you comment on that?

00:55:45.600 --> 00:55:48.050
&gt;&gt; Adam Gopnic: If I'm--
What I would say about it is,

00:55:48.050 --> 00:55:49.830
and it's something that
